column1: # Supplemental File S1 - Sheffield Nanopore Canonical ORF Sub-Genomic RNA Counts
# Canonical ORF counts for the Sheffield Nanopore dataset from clinical SARS-CoV-2 samples
# amplicons: The amplicon(s) that gave rise to the sub-genomic RNA
# gRNA_count: The number of genomic reads at this ORF
# sgRNA_HQ_count: The number of high quality reads supporting sub-genomic RNA at this ORF
# sgRNA_LQ_count: The number of low quality reads supporting sub-genomic RNA at this ORF
# sgRNA_LLQ_count: The number of low low quality reads supporting sub-genomic RNA at this ORF
# gRHPT: Genomic reads per hundred thousand mapped reads
# sgRPTg_HQ: High quality sub-genomic reads per thousand genomic
# sgRPTg_LQ: Low quality sub-genomic reads per thousand genomic
# sgRPTg_LLQ: Low low quality sub-genomic reads per thousand genomic
# sgRPTg_ALL: All sub-genomic reads per thousand genomic
# sgRPHT_HQ: High quality sub-genomic reads per hundred thousand mapped reads
# sgRPHT_LQ: Low quality sub-genomic reads per hundred thousand mapped reads
# sgRPHT_LLQ: Low low quality sub-genomic reads per hundred thousand mapped reads
# sgRPHT_All: All sub-genomic reads per hundred thousand mapped reads
